instance fidelity_and_validity_considerations : DTDFVocab:FidelityConsideration [
    base:desc "Model validity relies on four key assumptions: (1) perfect uniform temperature due to fan, (2) negligible wall heat accumulation, (3) constant specific heat of air, and (4) all power transferred to heatbed in Model A. Experimentally, temperature uniformity was confirmed with <7 °C variance, and Model B showed better prediction of thermal inertia. Calibration reduced residual errors, and sensitivity analyses were performed to quantify uncertainty associated with the free parameters."
]

